    <description>Description from the publisher:&amp;#10;&amp;#10;Tigers in the Snow depicts the nail-biting combat during the Battle of the Bulge in our Nations At War series. In December of 1944 Hitler launched Wacht am Rhein (Watch on the Rhine) catching the Allies completely by surprise. The plan was to surprise the Allies with an encirclement attack which would force the allies into a peace treaty with terms favorable for the Axis. The end result would what would be the last German offensive of World War 2.&amp;#10; Designed and developed by veteran Sean Druelinger, Tigers in the Snow will recreate some of the famous battles fought around Eisenborn Ridge in the north to Bastogne in the south, during the Battle of the Bulge. In the game, you can expect six gorgeous map boards with new terrain. Four counter sheets of 3/4&amp;quot; counters and various player aid cards. Special module rules covering limited fuel, German Commandos, and weather to name a few.&amp;#10;&amp;#10;</description>
